      "writtenOn": "2020-03-12T13:36:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "IMO - this test is trying to do too much and it is very hard for me to track what, essentially, are the expected inputs and the expected outputs.\n\nWhat makes it difficult is there is this somewhat arbitrary printing lines up with the parse token logic below.\n\nJust spitballing an idea here, but maybe make a series of helpers around CommandCollector and SetDelegateRun so the test can look something like:\n\n\nmockTest :\u003d newMockCommand()\nwriteStepStart(mockTest, 1, \"Do a thing\")\nwriteToStdOut(mockTest, \"log for step 1\")\n...\nwriteToStdErr(mockTest, \"err in step 2\")\n\nfor the timeout case above, there could also be:\nrunGoCode(func(ctx context.Context, cmd *exec.Command){\n  time.Sleep(10)\n})\n\nThen, to \"run\" that output, we see:\n\nres :\u003d td.RunTestSteps(t, false, runWithDefaultParsing(mockTest))\n\n// asserts begin here\n\nI think that will be a lot clearer and not depend on us running arbitrary bash/python code.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 113,
        "startChar": 32,
        "endLine": 125,
        "endChar": 2
      },
